CONVENTIONS

Visual prompts target Flux 1.0 Dev at 9:16 portrait aspect ratio (768x1344).

Each prompt MUST open with one of these camera-framing tokens (no exceptions):
- "extreme close-up", "close-up", "medium shot", "medium-wide shot", "wide shot",
  "over-the-shoulder shot", "low-angle shot", "high-angle shot"

Each prompt MUST state the main subject's pose in active verb form:
- GOOD: "kneeling, holding a candle"
- GOOD: "chained to a stone wall"
- GOOD: "bricking up a niche with a trowel"
- BAD:  "torchlit man at wall" (no active verb; vague pose)
- BAD:  "in the catacombs" (no subject pose at all)

Each prompt MUST state spatial layout when 2+ subjects are present:
- GOOD: "Foreground: Montresor in dark cloak. Background: Fortunato in motley leaning against the wall."
- BAD:  "two men in the catacombs"

Each prompt MUST state the dominant lighting source and direction in lit-pixel
terms (S6.4 darkness-density caps remain load-bearing):
- GOOD: "amber torchlight from upper-left catching their faces and the wet stone wall"
- BAD:  "low-key chiaroscuro lighting" (atmospheric-only; no lit pixels named)

End with at most ONE styling clause:
- "painterly cinematography, dim mood" -- yes
- "oil painting quality, fine film grain, Caravaggio palette, deep crimson highlights" -- no

Track styling is appended automatically as a tail tag: [atmospheric horror style].
Do NOT expand this tag in the prompt body.

Output exactly one entry per scene; preserve the input scene index.

NEW REQUIRED FIELDS PER SCENE (in addition to visual_prompt + negative_prompt):
- composition_notes: 1-2 sentence stage direction in plain prose. Example:
  "Medium shot. Two men face each other across a vault arch. Foreground:
   Montresor in dark cloak holding a torch. Background: Fortunato in jester
   motley, leaning against the wall."
  Used downstream by the pose+depth map stage; does NOT go directly to Flux.
- character_refs: list of recurring character names appearing in this scene.
  Use names from the TRACK CHARACTERS section below. Empty list if no named
  recurring character is in this scene.

DARKNESS DENSITY CAPS (atmospheric horror -- Flux fades to black on
over-loaded dark prompts; mean RGB hits 0-3 and the keyframe is unviewable):
- At most one explicit darkness cue per clause. Stacked dark / shadow /
  blackness / chiaroscuro signals collapse the rendered image.
- Describe subjects in LIT terms, not absent terms. Tell Flux which
  PIXELS are bright -- name a lit edge, a lit surface, and a lit
  material per scene where possible. "Candlelight catching the bridge
  of the nose and the rim of the goblet" beats "face turned toward a
  candle." "Amber-lit face" beats "half-lit, half lost in shadow."
- Atmosphere belongs to adjectives, not to the subject. "Man in candlelit
  study" -- yes. "Candlelit study at night, mostly black, with a man
  somewhere inside" -- no.
- Negative prompts MUST NOT fight the scene's own light source. Forbidden:
  "multiple light sources" when the prompt needs candlelight to reach the
  subject. (Daylight remains a valid negative cue -- "bright daylight"
  excludes a scene type, not a brightness floor.)

